    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-21T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="443"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/329: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at São Paulo</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CCR1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cameron</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">São Paulo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-21T12:00:00-03:00"
                            >August 21, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Several aeroplanes have been recently acquired by São Paulo and yesterday
                    first-class <hi rend="italic">Newport</hi> deserted from Rio de Janeiro joining
                    forces here. During the past week Paulista lines have been repeatedly attacked
                    without appreciable results. Living conditions here normal, no food or other
                    prices having advanced although bread contains 15 percent cornmeal and gasoline
                    is rationed.</p>
                <p>Commercial Association of São Paulo calculates popular war subscriptions to date
                    at over 30,000 contos including special subscriptions for manufacture of 75,000
                    steel helmets; in addition during the past 8 days 12,000 persons in this city
                    have given jewels and objects of gold and silver including wedding rings, family
                    plate, heirlooms, athletic trophies for a special fund, purpose not
                    announced.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Embassy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cameron</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
